title: PM Modi visits site of Morbi bridge collapse that killed 135 people
content: PM Narendra Modi on Tuesday visited the site of the Morbi bridge collapse which killed at least 135 people and injured around 100 others. Videos and photos from the site showed PM surveying the rescue work and meeting people carrying out the relief operations. He emphasised ensuring that all possible assistance was reaching the affected persons, PMO said.
author: Sakshita Khosla

title: PM Modi meets those injured in Morbi bridge collapse at civil hospital
content: PM Narendra Modi on Tuesday visited Morbi civil hospital where over 100 people injured in the suspension bridge collapse are admitted. At least 135 people were killed in the incident. Pictures showed PM Modi enquiring about a patient's health at the hospital. The hospital was painted overnight for PM Modi's visit.
author: Deepika Bhatt

title: England hand NZ their first defeat in T20 World Cup 2022, go 2nd on points table
content: England defeated New Zealand by 20 runs in their T20 World Cup 2022 Super 12 Group 1 match on Tuesday. With this, New Zealand suffered their first defeat in the ongoing tournament. New Zealand, England and Australia have accumulated five points each. New Zealand are on top of the table with superior net run-rate (NRR), while England are now second.
author: Anmol Sharma

title: Jos Buttler breaks record for smashing most runs for England in T20I cricket history
content: England white-ball captain Jos Buttler on Tuesday broke the record for scoring most runs for England in T20I cricket history. With his 73(47) against New Zealand in their T20 World Cup 2022 match on Tuesday, Buttler took his tally of runs in T20I cricket to 2,468. He overtook the previous record of 2,458 runs held by ex-England captain Eoin Morgan.
author: Anmol Sharma

title: Shubman Gill smashes highest score by an Indian in a T20 knockout match
content: Punjab opener Shubman Gill on Tuesday smashed his first-ever hundred in T20 cricket. The 23-year-old reached the three-figure mark off 49 deliveries and went on to score 126(55) against Karnataka in quarter-final match of Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy (SMAT) 2022. Shubman's 126 is also the highest score by an Indian in a T20 knockout match.
author: Anmol Sharma

title: What if I couldn't go to Harvard?: Co-founder as boAt becomes Harvard case study
content: Electronics maker boAt's Co-founder Aman Gupta on Tuesday took to Instagram to share the news that Harvard Business School has written a case study on boAt. "Harvard Nahee Jaa sake to Kya hua...apna kaam aur apnee company pahucha dee (What if I couldn't go to Harvard? I sent my company and work to Harvard)," he wrote.
author: Pragya Swastik

title: Income Tax Dept raids Cartier, Rolex retailer Kapoor Watch Company: Report
content: The Income Tax Department is conducting searches at Kapoor Watch Company, the Indian retailer of Audemars Piguet, Bvlgari, Cartier, Omega and Tag Heuer brands, as per a report. Sources said that around 20 premises were covered in this search which started on Monday morning. All the showrooms and premises of its promotors were covered in this search, the report added.
author: Ridham Gambhir

title: New pic of SRK & Deepika Padukone from 'Pathaan' sets leaks online
content: A new picture of Shah Rukh Khan and Deepika Padukone has leaked from the sets of their upcoming film 'Pathaan', which is going viral on social media platforms. Reportedly, the makers are planning to release the teaser of 'Pathaan' on November 2 to mark Shah Rukh's 57th birthday. The film, directed by Siddharth Anand, will release on January 25, 2023.
author: Kameshwari

title: Kartik Aaryan, Kiara Advani's pics from 'Satyaprem...' shoot get leaked
content: Leaked pics of Kartik Aaryan and Kiara Advani from their shoot for 'Satyaprem Ki Katha' have surfaced. Both of them are currently shooting in Ahmedabad. In one of the leaked pictures, Kiara can be seen sitting behind Kartik on a scooter. After 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 2', this will be the second time when Kiara and Kartik will be working together.
author: Amartya Sharma

title: Sh*t version of my film: Kolkata filmmaker on T-Series' 'Mister Mummy'
content: Kolkata filmmaker Akash Chatterjee has demanded T-Series to credit him for Riteish Deshmukh's film, titled 'Mister Mummy'. In a Facebook post, Akash Chatterjee alleged that T-Series "stole" the script of his film and came up with their "sh*t version" of it. He also shared that his story and concept are registered with Screenwriters Association, Mumbai.
author: Kameshwari

title: Twitter bans over 54,000 accounts in India for sexual, terror content
content: Twitter has banned 52,141 accounts in India for promoting child sexual exploitation and non-consensual nudity between August 26 and September 25. Twitter, now owned by Elon Musk, removed 1,982 accounts for promoting terrorism. In a monthly report, Twitter said it received 157 complaints from users in India in the same time-frame, out of which action was taken on 129 URLs.
author: Purnima Rajput

title: I appeal to innovators to develop techniques to conserve water: Prez Murmu
content: President Droupadi Murmu stressed on water conservation and appealed to scientists, town planners and innovators to try to develop techniques that will help conserve water resources. "There will be a need to effectively conserve water to meet the demands of our future generation and technology will play an important role in it," said the President.
author: Saurabh Pandey

title: Tata Motors' total sales rise by 15.5% to 78,335 units in October
content: Tata Motors said it registered a total sale of 78,335 units in October, witnessing a growth of 15.49%. The company had sold a total of 67,829 units in the same month last year. Tata said total domestic sales were at 76,537 units as against 65,151 units in the year-ago month, an increase of 17%.
author: Ambarish Awale

title: Fintech startup Decentro raises $4.7 million in Series A round
content: Decentro, a Y Combinator-backed startup that helps firms enter the fintech market, has secured $4.7 million in Series A funding round. The round was led by Singapore and US-based Rapyd Ventures, US-based Uncorrelated Ventures and Leonis VC from Europe. Angel investors, including CRED Founder Kunal Shah, Groww CEO Lalit Keshre and Gupshup CEO Beerud Sheth also participated in the round.
author: Purnima Rajput

title: Boss hits junior with clock for failing to meet monthly sales target in Mumbai
content: A 35-year-old man reportedly hit his junior with table clock after he failed to meet his monthly target of selling health insurance plans in Mumbai. Anand Singh resigned after missing the target and asked the accused, Amit Singh, for incentives, which he denied. When Anand demanded to discuss the matter before other employees, Amit lost his cool and hit him.
author: Swati Dubey

title: 24-yr-old youth arrested for looting 60 sacks of onions in Prayagraj
content: A 24-year-old youth was arrested for allegedly looting around 60 sacks of onions, along with his two accomplices, from two persons who were carrying the consignment from Prayagraj’s Jasra mandi to Pratapgarh on October 30. The youth, who was staying in Holland Hall hostel illegally, along with his accomplices purportedly held the victims captive for hours in the hostel.
author: Sakshi Sharma

title: Man dies after being pushed off building by robbers in Thane
content: A 26-year-old vegetable vendor died after he was pushed off a five-storey building by three unidentified men who allegedly robbed him of ₹12,000 in Mumbra, Thane. The incident happened when the deceased, Sujit Rajaram Gupta, had come to the building to collect empty vegetable crates, police said. A case has been registered under IPC sections 302 and 397.
author: Mohammad Anab

title: MMRDA launches 2nd of longest steel decks on Mumbai Trans Harbour Link
content: The Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA) launched the second of the longest (180 metre) orthotropic steel decks on the Mumbai Trans Harbour Link, a sea link that will connect South Mumbai to Navi Mumbai. The first 180-metre-long steel deck was launched in March 2022. These steel decks weigh as heavy as six large-sized aircraft.
author: Subhangi Singh

title: 22-yr-old Hyd woman who 'jumped' from 5th floor in UAE is alive: Embassy
content: A 22-year-old Hyderabadi woman who was assumed to be dead after falling from the fifth floor of a building in the UAE is currently undergoing treatment at a hospital, the Indian Embassy in Dubai said. Majlis Bachao Tehreek leader Amjed Ullah Khan said Afsha Begum, who worked as a housemaid in Ajman, had attempted suicide by jumping from the building.
author: Nidhi Sinha

title: Pune-based DPSU disposes of 258 tonnes of scrap, makes ₹1.48 crore
content: Pune-based Defence Public Sector Undertaking Munitions India Limited (MIL) has disposed of 258 tonnes of scrap from its various units. It's earned ₹1.48 crore from the scrap disposal, Indian Express quoted officials as saying. Moreover, 600 tonnes of scrap has been identified that will be disposed of soon. Notably, this was done as part of government's Special Campaign 2.0 initiative.
author: Dharini Mudgal

title: Macau tests 7 lakh residents after detecting 11 COVID-19 cases
content: Macau, the world's biggest gambling hub, carried out mass testing of its 7,00,000 residents on Tuesday after detecting 11 cases of COVID-19 in the past few days. Authorities had locked down a major casino in the city on Sunday, ordering staff and guests to stay inside until November 1. More than 1,500 people are reportedly sealed inside the casino.
author: Athira Sasidharan

title: Aus survivor of Halloween stampede in Seoul blames govt for mismanagement
content: Nathan Taverniti, 24-year-old Australian who survived stampede that killed over 150 people in Seoul, blamed officials for failing to employ crowd control measures despite anticipating massive turnout during Halloween festivities, The Associated Press reported. Taverniti said there should have been enough police on standby. "This incident is a result of government's mismanagement," Taverniti said.
author: Purnima Rajput

title: Finnish PM urges Hungary, Turkey to swiftly approve Finland, Sweden's NATO bids
content: Finland's Prime Minister Sanna Marin has urged Hungary and Turkey to swiftly approve Finland and Sweden's applications for NATO membership. The two Nordic countries asked to join NATO in May in response to Russian invasion of Ukraine but faced objections from Turkey, which accused the nations of giving shelter to groups it considers as terrorists.
author: Purnima Rajput

title: Adani Ports Q2 profit rises by 69% to ₹1,677.48 cr, revenue up by 33%
content: Adani Ports and Special Economic Zone (Adani Ports) reported a 68.5% year-on-year surge in September quarter profit to ₹1,677.48 crore. Consolidated revenue from operations grew by 32.8% to ₹5,210.80 crore as cargo volume increased by 15% year-on-year to 86.6 million metric tonnes. The revenue from port and SEZ activities rose to ₹4,609.29 crore.
author: Srishty Choudhury

title: UPL's Q2 net profit rises by 28% to ₹814 crore, revenue up by 18%
content: Global crop protection products manufacturer UPL posted a 28.4% year-on-year rise in consolidated net profit at ₹814 crore as against ₹633 crore in the corresponding quarter last fiscal. The company's consolidated revenue from operations surged by 18% year-on-year to ₹12,506 crore. UPL's stock fell by 2.14% on the NSE after the results and it closed 1.63% lower at ₹718.30 apiece.
author: Srishty Choudhury

title: Sun Pharma Q2 profit rises 10.5% YoY to ₹2,262 cr, revenue up 14%
content: Sun Pharmaceutical Industries on Tuesday reported a 10.5% year-over-year increase in its consolidated net profit to ₹2,262 crore in the July-September quarter. The company saw a nearly 14% rise in its total revenue from operations at ₹10,952 crore from ₹9,626 crore in the year ago quarter. Shares of the pharma major closed at ₹1,033 on BSE.
author: Bhawana Chaudhary
